problem: If $a = 8$, what is the value of $\left(16\sqrt[3]{a^2}\right)^{\frac 13}$?
chatgpt_solution:
We can solve this problem using the properties of exponents. We have  \begin{align*}
\left(16\sqrt[3]{a^2}\right)^{\frac 13} &= 16^{\frac 13}\left(\sqrt[3]{a^2}\right)^{\frac 13}\\
&= (\sqrt[3]{16})\sqrt[3]{(\sqrt[3]{a^2})}\\
&= (\sqrt[3]{16})(\sqrt[3]{(\sqrt[3]{a^2})})\\
&= (\sqrt[3]{16})\left(\sqrt[3]{\sqrt[3]{a^2}}\right)\\
&= (\sqrt[3]{16})(\sqrt[3]{\sqrt[3]{a^2}})\\
&= (\sqrt[3]{16})(\sqrt[9]{a^2})\\
&= (2)(\sqrt[9]{a^2})\\
&= (2)(\sqrt[9]{(a^2)})^1\\
&= (2)\left((a^2)^{\frac 19}\right)\\
&= \boxed{2a^{\frac 29}}.
\end{align*}
